This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with human trajectory prediction. It also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could be categorized under Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the modeling of interactions between agents, which could fall under Robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the use of a graph-based approach suggests that it could be categorized under Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
